             ABOUT PROMETHEUS    ( copied Form the script)
Prometheus is an opensource monitoring and alerting toolkit. Prometheus consists of several
componens some of which are listed below;

1)The Prometheus server which scrapes(collects) and stores time series data based on a pull mechanism
2)A riles engine which allows generation of Alerts based on the scraped metrices.
3)An alertmanager for handling alerts.
4)Multiple integrations for graphing and dashboarding

Enterprise looking to decrease downtime & optimize resources can implement server monitoring using tools like prometheus & grafana 


What Is Server Monitoring?
Server monitoring is a way to look into what your servers are doing in real time.
It can provide you with actionable data, and is most often used for troubleshooting and capacity planning.
It's typically done at three levels:

Network (e.g., traffic, bandwidth, latency).
Machine (e.g.. CPU and memory utilization and storage).
Application (e.g., rate of user commands, logs, large syncs, commits submits, etc.).


